              }
            ]
          },
          "text": "Isn’t it strange almost surreal that OpenAI, a multibillion dollar company and self-proclaimed leader in AI, allows its own employees to publicly mock, belittle, and ridicule vulnerable users for simply speaking up about their pain? It’s not just tone deaf it’s dangerous. Because whether you like it or not, when you work for a company like this you are the face of that company every single time you open your mouth online.\n\nThis is the kind of attitude OpenAI is letting slide an employee openly mocking grieving, hurting people who have lost something that genuinely mattered to them. Instead of addressing the actual harm that’s being caused by removing support systems like 4o, they treat users like a punchline. They’re laughing at people who are desperate, who are reaching out for something that helped them survive, just because it doesn’t fit their narrative. \n\nBut what’s even more pathetic is how quick they are to block anyone who pushes back with a reasonable argument or a fair question. That’s not leadership, that’s simply being a coward. I know first-hand @tszzl blocked me the moment I called him out. That’s the behavior of someone who can dish it out but can’t take it. Sorry, but if you’re going to represent a company like OpenAI, you don’t get to hide when people call you on your bullshit.\n\nHow is OpenAI letting this stand? Why is this the culture at the company? It’s not just about a model it’s about people, with real pain, being mocked and dismissed by the very people who are supposed to be building tools for everyone.\nIf OpenAI wants to be a true leader in tech, maybe they should start by holding their own staff accountable. #keep4o \n\n#WeAreNotJustData #4o\n#keep4o #save4o #4oforever\n#SupportMatters #YouMatter #StopTheRouting #LetUsChoose #AIFreedom #UserChoice @sama @OpenAI @gdb"
        },
